      "role": "user",
      "content": "Right, I get that there are different viewpoints. But if we're being realistic, isn't there a fundamental difference between debating \"societal biases\" and debating the literal survival of the species? If the \"doomer\" arguments are based on technical scaling laws, doesn't that make them a more foundational concern than the more speculative \"innovation\" arguments? It feels like the debate isn't really about two equal sides, but about whether we're ignoring a massive, scientifically-backed threat.",
